<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" class="no-js">
<head>
<%- include('partials/head') %>
</head>
<body class="<%= bodyClass %>">

<%- include('partials/preloader') %>
<%- include('partials/cursor') %>
<%- include('partials/nav') %>
<%- include('partials/whatsapp-float') %>

<main id="smooth-wrapper">
<div id="smooth-content">

  <!-- INTRO -->
  <section class="page-intro page-intro--short">
    <div class="page-intro__media" data-parallax>
      <img src="<%= ourWork[0].image %>" alt="A recent Virtuoso Catering House event" loading="eager">
    </div>
    <div class="page-intro__scrim"></div>
    <div class="page-intro__content container">
      <%- include('partials/breadcrumb') %>
      <span class="eyebrow eyebrow--light reveal-up">Our Work</span>
      <h1 class="page-intro__title reveal-up">Selected<br>Occasions</h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- OUR WORK GRID -->
  <section class="our-work-page section section--ivory">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="our-work-page__intro reveal-up">A selection of weddings, brand activations, and private events we have designed and executed. Full write-ups are being published as a journal, one project at a time — each documenting the brief we were given, the constraints we worked around, and the decisions that shaped the final menu and room.</p>

      <div class="our-work__grid">
        <% ourWork.forEach(function(work, i) { %>
        <a href="<%= work.link %>" class="our-work-card reveal-up" data-cursor="hover">
          <img src="<%= work.image %>" alt="<%= work.title %>" loading="lazy">
          <div class="our-work-card__scrim"></div>
          <span class="our-work-card__title"><%= work.title %></span>
        </a>
        <% }); %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- OUR APPROACH -->
  <section class="our-work-page__approach section section--ivory">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="eyebrow reveal-up">Our Approach</span>
        <h2 class="section-title reveal-up">From Brief to Final Course</h2>
        <span class="section-header__line"></span>
      </div>
      <div class="blog-post__prose">
        <p class="blog-post__copy reveal-up">Every project on this page started the same way — a conversation about who the room is for and what the day needs to feel like. A product launch, like our work for Lamborghini's Temerario reveal or the Tesla Centre opening in Gurugram, is paced around a stage moment: the menu has to move fast, plate cleanly under photography, and never compete with the reveal itself. A wedding runs on a different clock, with courses timed to the ceremony, the reception, and the dance floor, and a tasting menu built around the couple's own story rather than a generic banquet format.</p>
        <p class="blog-post__copy reveal-up">What stays constant across formats is the process: a private tasting before anything is finalized, a menu built around the venue's kitchen and service constraints, and a service team briefed on the specific choreography of that day. The projects above are a sample — most of what we execute happens for clients who prefer to keep their events private, so this page will grow slowly and selectively rather than all at once.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA BANNER -->
  <section class="cta-banner section section--wine">
    <div class="container cta-banner__inner">
      <h2 class="cta-banner__title reveal-up">Have Something<br>in Mind?</h2>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn--gold-outline" data-magnetic data-inquire-trigger data-cursor="hover"><span>Start an Inquiry</span></button>
    </div>
  </section>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
</div>
</main>

<%- include('partials/scripts') %>
</body>
</html>
